result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt:
ADDRESS INFO for Leah D Rosio
Current: 4120 McGraw Street, Wabeno, WI 54566 United States  (Effective: 07-27-2016)
Prior: 307 S Metonga Ave, Crandon, WI 54520

Called at 10:57 AM. Also called 13CF236. Leah Larock appears in person and in custody with attorney Jeff Joy. State appears by Charles Simono. State - resolved - 13CF236 - plead to count #2 as alleged, DRI counts #1 and #3; on 14CF07 - DRI entirely, joint recommedation of a withheld sentence and place on probation for 3 years with conditions of: 270 days in FC jail, $1000 fine plus costs and sucharges totalling $1538.00 - take bond posted - refund remainder, restitution of $61.20 owed to victim (JH) plus $6.12 in VW surcharge for a total restitition amount of $67.32 - take bond posted, AODA and follow thru, no consumption or possession of alcohol and no entry into any taverns or bars, maintain/obtain full time employment/school with verbage, 200 hours of community service, take all medications as prescribed by a treating physician or medical provider, no possession of any prescription drugs without a lawful prescription. Joy and Larock agree. Court dismisses and reads in 14CF07. Larock pleads G to count #2 as alleged on 13CF236. Court dismisses and reads in counts #1 and #3 on 13CF236. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her constitutional rights by entering her plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Joy makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Larock withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: #2 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 3 years with conditions of: 270 days in FC jail - huber allowed - eligible for community service under 973.09 (7m) - credit for 1 day only if revoked but will modify if counsel can find out more on credit, $1000 fine plus costs and sucharges totalling $1538.00 - take bond posted, restitution of $61.20 owed to victim (JH) plus $6.12 in VW surcharge for a total restitition amount of $67.32 - joint and several with co-defendants - take bond posted, AODA and follow thru, no consumption or possession of alcohol and no entry into any taverns or bars, maintain/obtain full time employment/school with verbage (5/10), obtain GED, 200 hours of community service, take all medications as prescribed by a treating physician or medical provider and in the manner in which they are prescribed, attend at least one AA/NA or similar treatment program each week, submit DNA sample with surcharge assessed - take bond posted, refund any remaining bond, no possession of firearms, no voting rights, right to appeal, adjourned.
Final pre-trial on May 14, 2014 at 10:00 am.

Called at 3:45 PM. Leah LaRock appears in person and in custody with attorney Jeff Joy. State appears by Charles Simono. State has filed Information that mirrors complaint in anticipation of a waiver of PH. Joy goes thru waiver of PH form with the defendant (off record). Back on record at 3:48. Court has waiver of PH form, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her right to PH, finds probable cause, binds over for trial. Joy has Information that mirrors complaints, waives reading of it, will proceed to ARGN and enters NG pleas to all counts. Court continues bond, accepts pleas, set for FPT on 5/14/14 at 10:00 AM.
Preliminary hearing on March 19, 2014 at 03:00 pm.

Called at 3:24 PM. Leah Larock appears via video from FOSO and her attorney Jeff Joy appears in person. State appears by Charles Simono. Larock and Joy have complaint but Joy has not gone over it with her. Court reads charges and penalties. Joy waives further reading, requests PH and will waive time limits. Court will consider time limits waived, sets matter for PH on 2/19/14 at 3:00 PM. State - bond - $5000 signature bond. Joy - no objections. Court sets bond at $5000 signature bond.
